A KZN hospital that was hard-hit by the second wave of COVID-19 is now offering rapid tests to the public. eNCA’s Lethiwe Mdluli reports. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - A KwaZulu Natal hospital that was hard-hit by the second wave of COVID-19 is now offering rapid tests to the public. The RK Khan Hospital in Chatsworth, Durban, faced a crisis a few weeks ago after many healthcare workers there tested positive. READ: Govt investigating shocking video filmed at KZN hospital Non-profit organisation, the Coronavirus Action Committee has stepped forward to help the hospital by offering their services at the testing site. Fore more details on the story, watch the video above.